\par }{\fs20 The Trickster is dead. The world has been saved from his evil. And yet strangely I have grown darker these 
\par past weeks. But Why? Comfort from old wine cellars has been easy enough to find, and loot at the expense 
\par of my rich neighbors still pays the bills. It is the simple life I had always wanted for myself.
\par 
\par No surprises \endash  and no world in need of rescue!
\par 
\par The Hammerites have promised a new mechanical eye. But what good is having their machine vision? 
\par Even when I had two perfectly normal human eyes I wasn't any richer than I am tonight!
\par 
\par Yet, as I write this, I am beginning to feel a shift in the air ...and not simply the rumbling of distant thunder. 
\par Perhaps it is just another crazy dream, but I can feel an inner gnawing saying that my fortunes are about to 
\par change ...that the }{\b\i\fs20 BIG}{\fs20  one is just around the corner where I'll finally know the true comfort and peace of 
\par mind that comes with becoming a genuinely wealthy man!}{\fs20\cf9 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\par }{\b\i Playing Information for The Enterprise
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\par }{\fs20 The Enterprise is a two-part mission. The first part is small, and the second part very large. 
\par 
\par The Thief 2 fog setting is entirely optional \endash  it looks cool either way. But setting for rain fall is a good 
\par idea since the sound of rain will be there whether or not you have Thief 2 set for rain.
\par 
\par The lighting may seem a tad bright. This done because not all machines display the game brightly enough. 
\par Use the - minus and + plus keys to adjust your screen for the right on-screen feeling.
\par 
\par EAX ambient sound is recommended. Adjusting }{\i\fs20 Audio}{\fs20  in the Thief 2 configuration screen may help 
\par headphone and other 2-speaker systems sound better.
\par 
\par Except for growing annoyances, there is no real differences between Normal, Hard, and Expert. So it\rquote s 
\par really a matter of how long you want to play, and how annoyed you are willing to become.
\par }{
\par }{\b\i Oddities and minor bugs that won\rquote t be fixed}{
\par 
\par }{\fs20 Sometimes Garrett will sink through a large descending freight lift platform while walking around if the 
\par platform is still moving. This doesn\rquote t seem to happen if you stay put and just enjoy the ride. It also does 
\par not seem to happen when ascending.
\par 
\par Sometimes on some computers there is no bashing sound when black-jacking an AI. In one case there was 
\par also a report about a loot item which made no sound when grabbed, and other rare instances of sound 
\par drop-outs. This only happens on some machines, and only rarely (I hope). Try setting audio channels in the 
\par Thief configuration to 16 instead of 24 if this is happening on your machine \endash  it might help.
\par 
\par Some of the workers may run off yet never find their way home \endash  mainly because \'93home\'94 is atop some
\par workbench, and AI don\rquote t seem to mark that as a place to call home. If you\rquote re ghosting or otherwise 
\par bashing your way through, then you\rquote ll rarely see this.
\par 
