\par 
\par }{\fs20\ul Ways to Crash the Mission (as in crashing the game or your computer)
\par }{\fs20 
\par }\pard \ql \li450\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin450\itap0 {\fs20 So far, I know of only a few areas that might cause a game crash:
\par 
\par 1. The upper (green portion) roof of the cathedral near the gable ends. 
\par Without a speed potion (or some fancy trick) you can't get up there anyhow, 
\par but somebody is bound to try.
\par 
\par 2. Jumping through the ice and looking back up at the cathedral. This is probably 
\par okay -- but in theory it might be a problem. At any rate, if you jump through 
\par the ice, Garrett will die anyway due to the current which sweeps him away and the 
\par freezing water.
\par 
\par 3. Scouting orbs have a wider field of view than the normal screen, and in some
\par places this was causing screen complexity crashes -- so they have been removed.
\par Speed potions were removed because this would allow access to all sorts of
\par evil locations (with respect to screen complexity).
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs20 
