\par }\pard\plain \s2\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel1\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\i Overview
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs20 
\par The Keepers have sent you to the \'93other side of time\'94 \endash  wherever that may be! Since time in the normal 
\par sense does not seem to exist in this place, your pocket watch is frozen and you are no longer getting sicker. 
\par 
\par But all is not well.
\par 
\par A permanent antidote can be found here somewhere. That is what the Keepers had hoped. So you must 
\par now explore this strange world to find what the answer may be \endash  and a way home.
\par 
\par Sometimes the cure is worse than the disease.
\par }{
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li0\ri0\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\i Playing Information for Oracle of the Prophets
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs20 
\par Do not save and reload when Garrett is attached to a CamVator. There are two CamVators in this mission 
\par and in both cases he will stop at the end and stay attached for a while. If you save and reload, at best, things 
\par may seem screwy; and at worst, you may break the mission so it can not be won. (For those not sure 
\par of what I mean \endash  \'93CamVator\'94 is short for }{\i\fs20 camera elevator}{\fs20 , where Garrett is attached to an invisible moving 
\par platform so the player\rquote s viewpoint can be transported as though watching a movie).
\par 
\par Gravity is that of another world \endash  about the same as Mars. It is part of the design to assume that Garrett can 
\par therefore climb on very steep angles and jump down from very high places which normally would be out of 
\par the question. Just because something looks nearly impossible, it may not be \endash  and may, in fact, be required.
\par 
\par Some odd fogging effects are implemented using a custom technique, so it does not matter if you have
\par these settings on or off in the Thief 2 configuration screen. It will work either way.
\par 
\par The lighting may seem a tad bright. This is done for those machines which display the game too darkly. 
\par If you usually run at maximum brightness, your game may not appear as realistic as I have planned. Use the 
\par minus (-) and plus (+) keys to adjust your screen for a proper on-screen feeling.
\par 
\par Because of the complexity of the terrain, EAX ambient sound is highly recommended. Typical 2-speaker 
\par or headphone use simply may not tell you enough about your threat situation, and you will be at a decided 
